# 07-bootstrapping

Generates files of the format:

    data-{data}.null_shuffle-{columns}_n-{N}_bsscalings.csv

Where `data` is the name of the input data, `columns` is the columns that were
shuffled (moree than one can be shuffled), and `N` is the number of repetitions.

Thus, this file is `1 + 16110*N` rows long.

I then manually zip them for space, which R can still read zipped CSVs.

The bootstrapping procedure can take a long time, so lower-N files exist for
testing purposes.
